I only gave 1 star because zero isn't an option.  So i tried to book with them a couple times. The first time didn't go through for som reason so I had to choose a different date by the time i found out it didn't go through. Then I booked with them again and even though I screen shoted the webpage and booking and it said food was included, when I got the email confirmation there was no food with my ticket forcing me to cancel and rebook again at a higher price.  Today was the scheduled day of the trip. My wife and I changed our schedules around from nights to days on one of her limited days off for this. We took a ferry over and tried to board the boat. They said that the boat was out of order due to maintenance issue and the cruise was canceled. They did not email us or anyone else in line as there were several other parties who had bought tickets that were there trying to board as well. If they would have notified us we would not of wasted our precious time turning around our schedules being sleep deprived to make the trip. We also would not have wasted our noney on a pointless ferry ride over and back.  When they did tell us that the cruise was canceled they did not want to give us a full refund. We had to argue with the employee and then the manager to give us a full refund for services we did not use. I don't know how they are staying in business through covid with such poor customer service and rude and beligerant staff. I don't recommend waisting your time with this company.

The worst experience. For one they do not have heat in any of the rooms that you are waiting in for a whole hour and a half. The only two rooms that were warm enough to stand in was the dinning room where your not allowed to go in until your eating time, and the Engine room that will have you smelling like grease and oil after standing in there for almost two hours. Then half the staff tell you there is no heat at all on the boat and the other half will tell you they don’t turn the heat on this time of year which is February and it was 50 degrees outside so being on the water it’s much colder. Just be prepared to bring a big coat hat scarf and gloves to stay warm while you wait.  The food reminds you something you get from Golden Corral.

The cruise along the Mississippi river aboard the historic Natchez Steamboat is definitely a must when visiting New Orleans.   We opted for the lunch cruise. I shouldn’t add any star, why? Because the boat is loaded with roaches. The first time we seen a roach was our first 15 mins on the boat. I didn’t make a loud outburst because I didn’t want to disturb everyone else dinner. Quietly, I notified the nearest waiter who called a manager to remove the roach off of the mirror. They gave us a free drink each because we was kind enough to not let the problem to be known. 10 minutes later another roach was crawling down the mirror. I didn’t make a loud outburst like the first incident for the same reason. This time they decided to let us get a free drinks for our entire duration on the boat. Fast forward, as we go to the bar to get a drink the bartender asked for a manager to come over so he can verify that we are being treated to free drinks for the remainder of the ride. Of course, the manager acted as if she didn’t know what was going on and she was the one who said we can get free drinks the remainder of our stay. Kiera (our waitress) was the best part of our stay. She was very friendly and made sure our cups stayed full. 10 stars for her. The boat needs a through cleaning with a pest control contractor.

We found a nice table where we enjoyed the view. The day we took the tour was foggy but it was perfect to take amazing photos. The tour was very informative, we learned a bunch of things. If you have kids that love big boats, they will enjoy this tour because they will see many huge cargoes boats. But if you have impatient kids, this might not be a ride for you, as the boat take its time to return. We did not have lunch on the boat, but the food smelled good. The band on board was playing jazz classics like Amstrong's songs.

Will never go on this tour again. My sister mom and I spent over 150 dollars to go on the tour. When we first got seated on the boat the tour guide came up to our table slammed his water and coffee down and said "I'm using this table." Never introduced himself, never said excuse me, or do you mind if I set these down. Fast forward 30 minutes later, we had a lady from New Zealand sit with us - we were trying to be nice and make conversation. On the previous boat tour we had gone on (the bigger one) we could listen to the guy talk when we wanted to or talk amongst ourselves and enjoy the scenery. Apparently this boat, do not talk, do not drink, do not do anything. Not only did we get reprimanded by the tour guy, he also started making derogatory jokes about us over the microphone. It wasn't until my sister heard him that we went downstairs into the cabin. It ended up starting a huge fight with my family and next thing I knew we were all in tears. We tried to go back to the place we paid for the tour, the lady gave us the number to the manager who runs the boat. We attempted calling three different times, and let voicemails and never heard anything back. WILL NEVER GO ON THIS TOUR AGAIN. Don't waste you money - if you go on one, go on the bigger boat. Waste of money, and so unprofessional.

Very informative & entertaining! I've worked & relaxed on both sides of the Mississippi River, so it was nice to see it all from the middle! The jazz band was very classy! You can view the engine room during operation & read all about it while in motion. The Captain & the Crew were very excellent hosts! It's an amazing way to see how goods are transported internationally on ships while enjoying a meal, a nice drink, & great music on a historical ride in New Orleans!  We rode the Natchez in July.  Just saying because you'll most likely see another steam boat on your trip.

When you're a tourist you must to touristy things, the Natchez cruise was well worth the price.  There's plenty of room to sit outside and enjoy the breeze or retire to the air conditioning inside the dining area.  Make sure to explore the engine room, it's hotter than blazes but it's got a real steam engine.  They're not making them like that any longer.

We really enjoyed the jazz cruise, will probably do the dinner cruise tomorrow.

I had my wedding here this past halloween. You pay for a package and they seem to really be on top of things until they get your first payment. After that your "wedding coordinator" is a pain in the a** . She is incompetant on so many levels. I even asked for someone else to assist me and was told she is the only wedding director and everyone else loves her. Well, I did not. The boat itself is beautiful and the wait staff is fantastic - The organizer is terrible. In the end I did not get several things "included" in the package and I organized her more than she did anything for me. Very disapointing- when I called to complain her "director" was as rude as she is an just kept telling me how everyone but me has good feedback. As if my issues were unjustified. First and Last time I ever do anything on this ship.
I do not think even a pig would like the food! Worse ever! Everything fried and no taste at all!

Ride the last true steamboat in NOLA, even though they use diesel to fuel the boat, it's real steam turning the paddles, unlike the other steamboat.  (they have a friendly competition though, no real rivalry)  The whimsical pipe organ on top lured us in as we walked along the water, watching it being played was a real treat.  During the trip, there was a guide who pointed out various points of interest over the PA system as you chug along up the Mississippi.  HOLD ONTO YOUR HAT or you will lose it.  Did not try any of the food onboard, but it smelled good.
